WEBVTT

00:00:02.031 --> 00:00:05.023
<v David> Hello everyone. Welcome
back to WordPress Accessibility Day.

00:00:05.048 --> 00:00:07.514
My name is David Vogelpohl at WP Engine

00:00:07.539 --> 00:00:09.409
and I'm proud to be
your host for this session:

00:00:09.433 --> 00:00:13.284
Much Ado About Captioning
Videos for WordPress and Beyond

00:00:13.309 --> 00:00:15.329
with Meryl K. Evans.

00:00:15.353 --> 00:00:18.575
Please feel free to add your questions
to the YouTube chat feed

00:00:18.845 --> 00:00:21.294
and we'll answer those
at the end of the presentation.

00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:23.558
I'm honored to introduce Meryl

00:00:23.583 --> 00:00:26.890
and her talk, Much Ado
About Captioning Videos.

00:00:26.915 --> 00:00:31.228
Born hearing-free, Meryl's first
encounter with captions came in 1983

00:00:31.252 --> 00:00:33.946
when she received a closed caption decoder.

00:00:33.971 --> 00:00:36.967
Because she depends on captions
to follow the video,

00:00:36.992 --> 00:00:39.927
she has seen the best
and worst of captions.

00:00:39.952 --> 00:00:41.840
Fast forward decades later,

00:00:41.840 --> 00:00:46.087
Meryl's digital marketing career has
come in handy in educating people

00:00:46.112 --> 00:00:49.999
about the benefits of captioning
videos and captioning them well.

00:00:50.443 --> 00:00:53.098
When she started making videos,
she wanted to caption them.

00:00:53.137 --> 00:00:54.761
As a self-employed professional,

00:00:54.785 --> 00:00:57.093
she worried about 
the investment to make that happen.

00:00:57.546 --> 00:00:58.788
Through trial and error,

00:00:58.812 --> 00:01:02.646
she figured out an effective process
for creating awesome captions

00:01:02.671 --> 00:01:05.760
that led her to create the
10 Rules of Great Captions.

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:10.975
And here to share that with you today,
I'd like to introduce Meryl K Evans.

00:01:11.754 --> 00:01:13.255
<v Meryl> Thank you, David.

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:14.743
Howdy, y'all.

00:01:14.767 --> 00:01:17.992
Before we start here
are a couple of things.

00:01:18.016 --> 00:01:20.749
First, there are a lot of visuals.

00:01:20.774 --> 00:01:23.426
If this is an accessibility issue

00:01:23.450 --> 00:01:26.884
with anyone needing
information or clarification,

00:01:26.908 --> 00:01:28.924
please contact me.

00:01:28.949 --> 00:01:33.087
Second, I want to quickly
mention audio description

00:01:33.111 --> 00:01:37.825
also referred to as
video description and AD.

00:01:37.850 --> 00:01:43.313
A narrator provides a description
of key visual elements in the video.

00:01:43.337 --> 00:01:46.580
While I won't cover it,
it is important to mention,

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:49.941
because it's an accessibility requirement.

00:01:49.965 --> 00:01:52.961
Thank you David
for bringing that to my attention.

00:01:52.986 --> 00:01:56.765
Third, thank you captioners and sponsors.

00:01:57.157 --> 00:02:02.149
Captioners, may the force be with you
in captioning this accent.

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:07.877
I'm Meryl, with two syllables,
and rhyme with pill not pull.

00:02:08.124 --> 00:02:10.924
I am a native Texan who lives in Plano,

00:02:10.949 --> 00:02:12.342
right next to Dallas.

00:02:12.830 --> 00:02:15.278
So I was born hearing-free,

00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:17.512
aka profoundly deaf.

00:02:17.822 --> 00:02:20.419
I am not capital D deaf,

00:02:20.888 --> 00:02:24.210
because I am not part of the deaf community

00:02:24.235 --> 00:02:26.059
and I don't know sign language.

00:02:26.512 --> 00:02:31.102
To listen, I rely on lip reading
and my bionic ear,

00:02:31.127 --> 00:02:35.271
which is a lot cooler than saying
Cochlear Implant,

00:02:36.049 --> 00:02:38.628
aside from being a caption pusher,

00:02:38.652 --> 00:02:40.822
I am a Digital Marketing Freelancer.

00:02:41.314 --> 00:02:44.152
This is what my first
caption decoder looked like.

00:02:44.176 --> 00:02:48.375
It was this clunky thing
that sat on top of the TV.

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:52.633
Little did I know, it was
going to change my life.

00:02:53.121 --> 00:02:57.776
We'll cover the other reasons to caption
besides accessibility,

00:02:57.801 --> 00:03:00.660
because some don't think
it's a good enough reason.

00:03:01.136 --> 00:03:02.731
Crazy, right?

00:03:02.978 --> 00:03:04.311
But that's reality.

00:03:04.668 --> 00:03:08.587
I see a lot of posts where people ask
if they should caption their video.

00:03:08.944 --> 00:03:12.623
Unfortunately, captions
don't just magically appear.

00:03:12.904 --> 00:03:14.043
If only.

00:03:14.356 --> 00:03:17.251
Automatic craptions don't count, y'all.

00:03:17.811 --> 00:03:20.252
Look at this auto-craption,

00:03:20.276 --> 00:03:22.899
I definitely did not say that.

00:03:22.923 --> 00:03:25.265
So we'll dig into how captions work.

00:03:25.845 --> 00:03:29.173
You have many options
for captioning your videos.

00:03:29.198 --> 00:03:30.697
We'll cover those.

00:03:30.722 --> 00:03:35.697
And finally, great captions are
more than just capturing the audio.

00:03:35.904 --> 00:03:38.006
Why should you caption your video?

00:03:38.031 --> 00:03:41.976
The number one answer
is accessibility, of course.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:43.749
That should be enough, right?

00:03:44.083 --> 00:03:45.654
Alas, it's not

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:50.678
and the second most popular reason is
to help second language learners.

00:03:50.703 --> 00:03:53.027
Many focus on these two reasons

00:03:53.052 --> 00:03:54.642
and for some creators,

00:03:54.666 --> 00:03:59.128
it's not enough to justify their
time and resources for captioning.

00:04:00.065 --> 00:04:02.587
<v David> All right, we're just
trying to get the screen sharing going.

00:04:03.319 --> 00:04:05.837
Okay, there we go. Awesome.
<v Meryl> Yeah.</v>

00:04:05.862 --> 00:04:07.580
Sorry about that everybody.

00:04:07.604 --> 00:04:09.258
<v David> Yeah.</v>
<v Meryl> Technology, right.</v>

00:04:10.679 --> 00:04:15.774
When you share the other reasons,
it makes creators rethink captioning.

00:04:16.266 --> 00:04:20.389
Only 6% of the world's population
is deaf or hard of hearing.

00:04:20.845 --> 00:04:25.772
Naturally, creators may think their
audience doesn't include those groups,

00:04:26.129 --> 00:04:27.955
or it's too small to bother.

00:04:28.645 --> 00:04:30.397
But they'll change their mind

00:04:30.430 --> 00:04:34.627
when you share that people
who are deaf and hard of hearing

00:04:34.652 --> 00:04:38.059
are not the primary users of captions.

00:04:38.337 --> 00:04:42.487
A survey has found that
80% of those using captions,

00:04:42.512 --> 00:04:46.019
are not deaf or hard of hearing.

00:04:46.043 --> 00:04:49.095
That you reach more people with captions.

00:04:49.680 --> 00:04:50.811
You want the caption,

00:04:50.835 --> 00:04:55.600
because it greatly increases the chances
of people watching more of your video.

00:04:56.480 --> 00:04:59.598
Lately a lot of data has popped up
that shows

00:04:59.622 --> 00:05:01.966
more people turning off the sound

00:05:01.991 --> 00:05:04.559
especially watching videos in public.

00:05:05.479 --> 00:05:08.130
But what about if they're
watching in private?

00:05:08.807 --> 00:05:12.071
A good number of them
still keep the sound off.

00:05:12.912 --> 00:05:15.753
My youngest is a member of Gen Z,

00:05:15.778 --> 00:05:17.437
and he has ADHD.

00:05:17.896 --> 00:05:20.226
He does well with multitasking.

00:05:20.250 --> 00:05:24.458
He'll be on his phone, with Nintendo
while watching a captioned video.

00:05:24.880 --> 00:05:29.617
Many of his friends do the same thing
regardless if they have ADHD.

00:05:30.189 --> 00:05:35.009
It also helps those with language
processing disorders and other differences.

00:05:35.462 --> 00:05:38.722
Some people with none
of these differences say

00:05:38.746 --> 00:05:41.659
they use captions
because it helps them focus.

00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:48.596
Besides, even hearing can be affected
on a temporary or situational basis.

00:05:49.192 --> 00:05:53.419
A cold, an ear infection
can change a person's hearing.

00:05:53.903 --> 00:05:57.798
Think you one really rowdy
restaurant, bar and gym.

00:05:58.436 --> 00:06:01.063
Masks are everywhere nowadays.

00:06:01.425 --> 00:06:03.439
A lot of people who can hear

00:06:03.464 --> 00:06:08.745
say they have a hard time understanding
people talking with a mask on.

00:06:09.190 --> 00:06:12.997
What do Hulu, Netflix, Harvard,

00:06:13.021 --> 00:06:17.820
MIT and Pornhub have in common?

00:06:18.281 --> 00:06:21.400
They have all been sued
over the lack of captions.

00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:25.487
Yes, you heard right.
I said Pornhub.

00:06:26.022 --> 00:06:30.236
A man sued Pornhub,
because videos were not captioned.

00:06:30.640 --> 00:06:34.687
He's probably one of those
who reads Playboy for the articles, right?

00:06:34.717 --> 00:06:36.151
[unintelligible]

00:06:36.643 --> 00:06:39.809
Contrary to what 
these companies may think,

00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:43.254
it's not cheaper to deal with law suits

00:06:43.279 --> 00:06:46.826
over fitting accessibility
into the organization.

00:06:47.351 --> 00:06:49.295
Caption users are passionate.

00:06:49.795 --> 00:06:53.270
They will speak loudly and fully comprehend

00:06:53.536 --> 00:06:55.853
it can hurt the company's reputation.

00:06:56.210 --> 00:07:00.958
That the lack of captioning
costs more than the law suit.

00:07:01.451 --> 00:07:04.101
Captions also increase brand awareness.

00:07:04.831 --> 00:07:08.638
Any opportunity to help people
remember your brand is a must do

00:07:08.663 --> 00:07:10.083
in those noisy rooms.

00:07:10.424 --> 00:07:16.541
And last, but not least, when you close
captions, as opposed to open captions,

00:07:16.819 --> 00:07:19.704
caption can boost SEO.

00:07:20.581 --> 00:07:22.982
Captions don't magically show up.

00:07:23.549 --> 00:07:25.175
They require two things:

00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:28.478
the video, 
the text file with the captions.

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:32.227
Even if you use
YouTube's automatic captions,

00:07:32.603 --> 00:07:35.432
YouTube usually creates 
a caption text file.

00:07:35.741 --> 00:07:38.560
You can download it and use it elsewhere.

00:07:39.373 --> 00:07:41.750
The way to add caption to a video

00:07:41.774 --> 00:07:45.174
is to create a text file
that goes with the video.

00:07:45.555 --> 00:07:52.847
The formats that you and I will use
most likely are SRT and WebVTT.

00:07:53.474 --> 00:07:55.835
There are tons of formats.

00:07:56.617 --> 00:08:00.419
The captions are in a text file
that you can open in a text editor.

00:08:00.799 --> 00:08:03.661
The magic happens in
the time column

00:08:04.197 --> 00:08:07.689
that tells the caption
when to appear and disappear.

00:08:08.212 --> 00:08:12.931
When you play the videos that uses
the caption file is called closed caption.

00:08:13.582 --> 00:08:15.400
Since this is a text file

00:08:16.042 --> 00:08:18.030
search engine can read it.

00:08:18.621 --> 00:08:22.810
That's how you get the benefit of SEO
with closed captions.

00:08:23.556 --> 00:08:27.666
You have many options
for adding caption to a video.

00:08:27.971 --> 00:08:32.041
I am sharing one example,
so you can see the process.

00:08:32.636 --> 00:08:35.061
This video shows you
how to do it on YouTube,

00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:38.462
since it's free and almost
everyone has an account.

00:08:39.111 --> 00:08:45.542
[Video plays with captions]

00:09:02.425 --> 00:09:05.275
[Mouse clicking]

00:09:11.055 --> 00:09:12.976
[Video plays with captions]

00:10:08.152 --> 00:10:12.511
<v Meryl (in video)> Hey y'all.
Meryl Evans here creating a short clip

00:10:12.536 --> 00:10:16.004
to show you how to caption a video.

00:10:16.029 --> 00:10:18.485
You can copy and paste the script.

00:10:19.091 --> 00:10:23.328
Boom and then automatic
captions do the work

00:10:23.362 --> 00:10:25.290
and then edit it.

00:10:25.315 --> 00:10:27.345
[Video continues with captions]

00:10:31.742 --> 00:10:34.291
<v Meryl (in video)> Hey y'all, Meryl Evans…

00:10:41.784 --> 00:10:44.982
And copy and paste the script.

00:10:48.451 --> 00:10:53.336
Boom let automatic captions
do the work and then…

00:10:55.225 --> 00:11:00.290
[Video continues with captions]

00:11:17.456 --> 00:11:18.468
<v Meryl> Two points.

00:11:18.492 --> 00:11:23.035
First, did you notice the line that
the captions got shorter on the left?

00:11:23.480 --> 00:11:26.100
and then that the caption lines matter.

00:11:26.125 --> 00:11:27.767
More on that shortly.

00:11:27.822 --> 00:11:31.433
The point is, 
don't rely on YouTube to set the length.

00:11:32.227 --> 00:11:33.409
The second point,

00:11:34.270 --> 00:11:37.526
at the end when I selected
to download the video

00:11:37.560 --> 00:11:42.392
I could download the SRT, VTT or SBV.

00:11:42.829 --> 00:11:45.694
SBV is YouTube caption format.

00:11:46.249 --> 00:11:50.601
To add a video from
YouTube or Vimeo to WordPress,

00:11:50.625 --> 00:11:55.000
you copy the videos URL
and paste it into WordPress.

00:11:55.270 --> 00:11:57.096
No need for caption file.

00:11:57.524 --> 00:12:00.996
However, you might need the caption file
for other things

00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:04.127
things such as posting videos
on LinkedIn or Facebook.

00:12:05.600 --> 00:12:09.729
Now this is what the SRT file
I downloaded from YouTube

00:12:10.240 --> 00:12:12.387
at the end of the video looks like.

00:12:13.101 --> 00:12:17.312
SRT is short for SubRip Subtitle file.

00:12:18.316 --> 00:12:23.319
Linkedin, YouTube, Facebook, Vimeo
and many of the platforms accept this.

00:12:23.819 --> 00:12:27.839
You'll see it has sequence number—
one, two, three, four, five

00:12:28.462 --> 00:12:29.972
followed by a time column.

00:12:31.209 --> 00:12:35.524
"This video will show you
how to" is the first caption.

00:12:35.874 --> 00:12:39.468
It shows up when the video hits
the first time code

00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:44.470
and it goes away when the video
reaches the second time code.

00:12:44.946 --> 00:12:46.946
Let's check out another format.

00:12:47.747 --> 00:12:50.900
This is an example of WebVTT file.

00:12:51.285 --> 00:12:54.075
It's modeled after SRT,

00:12:54.099 --> 00:12:56.706
but it takes captions a step further

00:12:56.731 --> 00:12:59.727
by allowing you to format the text,

00:12:59.751 --> 00:13:01.932
to choose the positioning and other things.

00:13:02.273 --> 00:13:05.514
This is the same text
in the previous example

00:13:05.539 --> 00:13:09.193
except it follows VTT
formatting.

00:13:09.519 --> 00:13:12.930
No sequence numbers like the SRT file,

00:13:12.955 --> 00:13:18.166
just the time code showing the
start and end time for each caption.

00:13:18.959 --> 00:13:21.083
Who wants to type all that out?

00:13:22.189 --> 00:13:28.056
So what other ways can we create
a text file to add caption to a video?

00:13:28.952 --> 00:13:33.170
You have three options for captioning
will create the text file.

00:13:33.195 --> 00:13:36.448
You can Do-it-Yourself with tools
like I just did,

00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:39.703
use the company
that offer captioning services,

00:13:40.151 --> 00:13:43.580
or find a tool that
automatically captions the video

00:13:43.929 --> 00:13:45.688
and edit those captions.

00:13:46.183 --> 00:13:49.177
A lot of people ask how long
it takes to caption the video?

00:13:49.772 --> 00:13:51.158
You'll hate my answer.

00:13:51.884 --> 00:13:52.940
It depends.

00:13:53.876 --> 00:13:56.795
The biggest factor is
the length of the video

00:13:56.820 --> 00:13:58.772
and how much audio it has.

00:13:59.283 --> 00:14:03.973
Simply put, the longer the video
and the more audio it has,

00:14:03.998 --> 00:14:05.927
the longer it will take to caption it.

00:14:06.379 --> 00:14:08.669
Let's quickly take a look at each one.

00:14:09.438 --> 00:14:12.167
The list of captioning tools is long

00:14:12.192 --> 00:14:14.572
and these are just a few examples

00:14:15.020 --> 00:14:19.249
and the best captioning tool is…

00:14:20.614 --> 00:14:24.034
it depends on your
processes and preferences.

00:14:24.558 --> 00:14:29.796
Personally I use YouTube,
because it has the easiest user interface.

00:14:30.391 --> 00:14:33.857
Youtube also has automatic captions,

00:14:34.112 --> 00:14:38.825
but I never ever rely on auto-craptions,

00:14:38.850 --> 00:14:40.298
as I call them.

00:14:40.322 --> 00:14:42.816
They don't like my accent very much.

00:14:43.871 --> 00:14:46.335
You know who creates the best caption?

00:14:46.705 --> 00:14:48.237
Humans do.

00:14:48.594 --> 00:14:52.020
So thank you to the person
captioning this right now.

00:14:52.750 --> 00:14:58.306
Some of these captioning and
transcription services are 100% human.

00:14:58.941 --> 00:15:03.054
Some use automated
tools called ASR,

00:15:03.661 --> 00:15:07.440
Automatic Speech Recognition.

00:15:07.440 --> 00:15:12.072
And others may use the mix of
artificial and human intelligence.

00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:14.560
You submit your video to the service

00:15:14.560 --> 00:15:16.919
and they'll send you the caption file.

00:15:16.943 --> 00:15:20.387
The output and the turnaround time
depends on the service.

00:15:21.040 --> 00:15:24.334
I'm sorry for the curse word in the photo.

00:15:24.358 --> 00:15:26.612
I did not say that word.

00:15:26.636 --> 00:15:28.909
It is auto-craption's fault.

00:15:29.342 --> 00:15:33.482
Of course the photo on the right
has the correct caption.

00:15:33.946 --> 00:15:38.296
The accuracy in automatic captioning
is not good enough.

00:15:38.321 --> 00:15:43.943
Oftentimes it has no punctuation
and looks like one big blob of text

00:15:43.968 --> 00:15:45.360
with incorrect words.

00:15:46.158 --> 00:15:50.626
The good news, there are more app to
help you add captioning.

00:15:50.651 --> 00:15:54.453
The bad news, is they have
caption formatting options

00:15:54.477 --> 00:15:58.608
that you can't read or
distract you from the video.

00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:02.485
Captioning audio
is only part of the formula.

00:16:02.509 --> 00:16:06.590
For awesome captions,
quality is the other half.

00:16:07.074 --> 00:16:10.356
The reason why great captions are boring

00:16:10.388 --> 00:16:13.539
is because they let the video be the star.

00:16:13.888 --> 00:16:16.432
They don't fight for the spotlight.

00:16:17.158 --> 00:16:19.599
When it comes to
posting videos on WordPress,

00:16:19.623 --> 00:16:21.015
two things to keep in mind.

00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:25.944
One is to have player control
with the start and stop button.

00:16:26.375 --> 00:16:29.248
No auto play please.

00:16:29.273 --> 00:16:30.625
Even I don't like it.

00:16:31.201 --> 00:16:36.619
It creates a better user experience
when the user can play and stop the video.

00:16:37.151 --> 00:16:41.584
The second part, is of
course caption your video.

00:16:42.183 --> 00:16:45.514
You can upload a video
and caption file to WordPress,

00:16:46.149 --> 00:16:53.374
but the markup is more involved than simply
paste in the URL of a video into WordPress.

00:16:54.303 --> 00:16:59.288
Besides, your website service
may have a file upload limit

00:16:59.313 --> 00:17:03.073
and it may not be optimized
for serving videos.

00:17:03.098 --> 00:17:07.457
While it means, I have to depend
on Youtube not going down,

00:17:07.481 --> 00:17:10.453
it takes some stress off my website.

00:17:11.200 --> 00:17:15.516
Most of you probably already know
this process. This will be quick.

00:17:16.209 --> 00:17:19.216
These steps work for Vimeo and VideoPress.

00:17:19.724 --> 00:17:21.629
Here's what it looks like in WordPress.

00:17:22.179 --> 00:17:24.470
First, select YouTube for the block.

00:17:24.958 --> 00:17:30.215
Second, copy and paste the YouTube URL
into the WordPress editor

00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:31.573
and ta dah.

00:17:32.291 --> 00:17:34.267
Vimeo works the same way.

00:17:34.851 --> 00:17:37.767
If you enter the caption
on YouTube or Vimeo

00:17:38.442 --> 00:17:40.878
they'll show up on your
WordPress website.

00:17:41.334 --> 00:17:45.341
If you want to upload the
video to the WordPress website,

00:17:45.683 --> 00:17:52.113
it typically requires using either HTML
or adding open captions.

00:17:52.138 --> 00:17:55.573

Here is an example of HTML5

00:17:55.598 --> 00:17:57.408
for adding a captioned video,

00:17:58.324 --> 00:18:03.332
"kind", which is highlighted
in gray, the first highlight,

00:18:04.412 --> 00:18:07.033
can be subtitles or captions.

00:18:07.057 --> 00:18:08.971
I use subtitles here,

00:18:08.995 --> 00:18:15.533
so you can see it needs to have
a srclang for each language.

00:18:15.558 --> 00:18:18.851
I use ES which is Spanish.

00:18:18.876 --> 00:18:22.383
You can also customize captions with CSS.

00:18:23.002 --> 00:18:25.776
There is no one standard
for great captions.

00:18:25.800 --> 00:18:28.000
You'll find guidelines
for caption quality

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:31.175
from Described and Caption Media Program,

00:18:31.842 --> 00:18:35.576
FCC, WCAG's POUR

00:18:35.600 --> 00:18:41.742
which stands for: Perceivable,
Operable, Understandable, Robust.

00:18:41.767 --> 00:18:46.108
I created the Caption10 best practices,
before I found these guidelines.

00:18:46.537 --> 00:18:51.353
The Caption10 includes many
of the list of these guidelines

00:18:51.378 --> 00:18:54.274
and enhances them based on my experience.

00:18:54.560 --> 00:18:57.566
If you're like me,
you learn from example,

00:18:57.591 --> 00:19:01.277
so here's the number one rule
of awesome captions

00:19:01.302 --> 00:19:02.901
and this shows you why.

00:19:03.436 --> 00:19:06.210
One side contains great captions,

00:19:06.234 --> 00:19:10.416
the other painful captions
I have seen in video.

00:19:10.924 --> 00:19:14.692
One thing to know, the right side
has many different captions

00:19:14.716 --> 00:19:16.587
since the
[unintelligible] is important,

00:19:16.612 --> 00:19:18.990
but I wanted to show you actual examples

00:19:19.014 --> 00:19:22.017
of what creators have
used in their captions.

00:19:22.300 --> 00:19:26.578
[Video plays with captions]

00:19:48.239 --> 00:19:50.656
<v Meryl> Readability has four components:

00:19:50.680 --> 00:19:55.760
size, color, background, which
is the color behind the text.

00:19:55.760 --> 00:20:00.084
In fact, captions without a background
are hard to read.

00:20:00.108 --> 00:20:02.770
When I was looking for exercise videos,

00:20:02.795 --> 00:20:05.955
I found captioned video from two companies.

00:20:05.979 --> 00:20:09.871
Peloton won me over,
because they were more readable.

00:20:09.896 --> 00:20:12.336
The other one did not have a background.

00:20:13.411 --> 00:20:18.624
The next will explain
why I say auto-craption.

00:20:19.123 --> 00:20:25.107
[Video plays with captions]

00:21:07.969 --> 00:21:10.703
<v Meryl> Auto-craptions are good for a few laughs,

00:21:10.728 --> 00:21:14.494
but they're not so funny
when you're trying to watch a video.

00:21:15.049 --> 00:21:18.990
I often quit watching videos
when the captions aren't good.

00:21:19.022 --> 00:21:21.875
It turns off many
other viewers too.

00:21:22.307 --> 00:21:28.047
They just write, any kind of craptions
are no better than no captions.

00:21:31.500 --> 00:21:37.135
When you watch this next video cover up
the left side and see what happens.

00:21:38.463 --> 00:21:43.407
[Video plays with captions]

00:22:05.023 --> 00:22:06.734
<v Meryl> How was that experience?

00:22:07.666 --> 00:22:11.419
As I said, I can tell when
the captions are out of sync,

00:22:11.444 --> 00:22:13.765
even when I'm not wearing my bionic ear.

00:22:15.173 --> 00:22:19.022
Yes size matters.

00:22:19.495 --> 00:22:21.160
Here's why.

00:22:21.185 --> 00:22:24.784
Cover up the left side if you dare.

00:22:25.604 --> 00:22:29.690
[Video plays with captions]

00:23:21.096 --> 00:23:23.334
<v Meryl> Remember the
YouTube video where I show that

00:23:23.359 --> 00:23:26.104
line's length and breaking points

00:23:26.167 --> 00:23:31.868
are two areas I failed at in my
early days to start self-captioning,

00:23:31.893 --> 00:23:33.795
because I let YouTube do it.

00:23:34.446 --> 00:23:37.279
Bad idea, humans know best.

00:23:37.747 --> 00:23:43.025
Length has many factors and videos often
break this rule for any of these reasons.

00:23:43.440 --> 00:23:47.581
More than one or two lines makes it hard
not to lose your place while reading,

00:23:48.152 --> 00:23:51.801
and from one or two lines
up to 32 characters per line.

00:23:52.468 --> 00:23:55.262
As for alignment, the important thing

00:23:55.600 --> 00:23:59.491
is to keep it consistent
for the entire video.

00:24:00.032 --> 00:24:01.952
Which position do you prefer,

00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:04.382
top or bottom?

00:24:04.406 --> 00:24:08.771
In this one, you might want to
hide one side for about eight seconds

00:24:08.796 --> 00:24:11.617
and then look at the other side
for the remainder.

00:24:11.642 --> 00:24:17.815
[Video plays with captions]

00:24:46.910 --> 00:24:50.522
<v Meryl> Don't worry, your
volume won't suddenly stop working.

00:24:50.547 --> 00:24:52.649
This video has no sound

00:24:52.674 --> 00:24:56.461
to show you the
importance of sound.

00:24:56.936 --> 00:24:59.710
The left side shows
the correct way to do it.

00:25:00.583 --> 00:25:05.502
The right side shows what happens
when you don't caption the sound.

00:25:08.122 --> 00:25:14.273
[Silent video plays with captions]

00:26:29.920 --> 00:26:34.197
[On-screen text] This was a simple video to
show the importance of sound.

00:26:35.888 --> 00:26:40.357
<v Meryl> Noting silence or
background music is so important.

00:26:40.382 --> 00:26:44.888
One episode of a TV show
went on and on without captions.

00:26:44.913 --> 00:26:47.287
I didn't have my bionic ear on,

00:26:47.311 --> 00:26:51.430
so I was wondering
if I was missing a voiceover or a song.

00:26:51.930 --> 00:26:56.398
Don't leave humans wondering
if the captions are messed up.

00:26:57.627 --> 00:27:00.839
At the start of a TV show
when introducing the stars,

00:27:00.863 --> 00:27:03.735
the caption and the chyron really overlap.

00:27:03.760 --> 00:27:07.961
In fact, many shows
move the caption up temporarily

00:27:07.985 --> 00:27:09.749
and then bring them back down

00:27:09.774 --> 00:27:13.297
or they move the chyron above the caption.

00:27:13.767 --> 00:27:20.918
[Video plays with captions]

00:28:18.659 --> 00:28:23.237
<v Meryl> Now, let's take a look at
what voice means and why it matters.

00:28:23.262 --> 00:28:26.453
I'm going to turn off
your sound for this one.

00:28:26.478 --> 00:28:28.922
The caption will tell the story.

00:28:32.220 --> 00:28:36.268
[Silent video plays with captions]

00:29:52.087 --> 00:29:56.817
<v Meryl> The next time that singer showed
up on America's Got Talent it was terrible.

00:29:57.190 --> 00:30:00.182
This time they didn't even
caption the voice changes.

00:30:02.611 --> 00:30:07.849
You never want to confuse your viewers and
have them wondering who said that.

00:30:08.119 --> 00:30:11.221
The quality of the video clip
is in the back.

00:30:11.246 --> 00:30:15.708
The irony is I was trying to replace it
with the better quality video,

00:30:15.733 --> 00:30:17.653
but the captions were terrible.

00:30:17.678 --> 00:30:18.804
Take a look.

00:30:19.249 --> 00:30:26.855
[Video plays with captions]

00:31:24.951 --> 00:31:28.562
<v Meryl> The video showed off three
examples for identifying the speakers.

00:31:29.427 --> 00:31:34.041
You can put captions under speakers
when you use open caption or VTT

00:31:34.066 --> 00:31:36.204
which allows you to control positioning.

00:31:36.787 --> 00:31:39.238
Here's the last one
of the caption10.

00:31:39.262 --> 00:31:41.090
This session is the live event

00:31:41.115 --> 00:31:44.695
like all live events
it uses scrolling captions.

00:31:44.720 --> 00:31:46.207
That can't be avoided,

00:31:46.231 --> 00:31:49.508
however, I think scrolling captions
in recorded videos

00:31:49.533 --> 00:31:53.279
that will not pop-in,
is easier on the eyes,

00:31:53.318 --> 00:31:59.732
less detracting and most importantly
lets people read at their own pace.

00:32:00.173 --> 00:32:01.877
These videos are not in sync.

00:32:01.902 --> 00:32:03.512
It was a challenge to make this.

00:32:04.250 --> 00:32:07.286
The left is the Pop-in
and the right is the Scrolling.

00:32:07.310 --> 00:32:09.219
I'm turning the sound off for this one.

00:32:10.958 --> 00:32:18.696
[Silent video plays with captions]

00:32:47.680 --> 00:32:51.438
<v Meryl> Accessibility should be
reason enough to caption videos.

00:32:51.462 --> 00:32:53.211
It's the right thing to do.

00:32:53.236 --> 00:32:56.097
Of course, that's not enough for everyone

00:32:56.121 --> 00:32:58.914
and they're not all required
to comply with the law.

00:32:59.644 --> 00:33:03.148
Captioning is cheap, definitely
cheaper than a lawsuit.

00:33:03.172 --> 00:33:07.698
With all the tools available,
it's easier and more affordable.

00:33:08.372 --> 00:33:10.265
Caption expands your reach,

00:33:10.305 --> 00:33:14.277
boosting your brand and company
reputation and prevents lawsuits.

00:33:14.737 --> 00:33:19.434
It's possible to profit off
captions as Peloton did

00:33:19.459 --> 00:33:21.101
when I became a member.

00:33:21.126 --> 00:33:25.264
Because it not only had
captions, but high quality captions.

00:33:25.716 --> 00:33:30.763
Looking here, I'm talking about
them spreading their name and brand.

00:33:32.890 --> 00:33:37.198
What can we do to get captions
to spread faster than Covid19?

00:33:37.223 --> 00:33:39.014
If you see a captioned video

00:33:39.038 --> 00:33:42.291
leave a comment
thanking the creator for captions

00:33:42.315 --> 00:33:45.817
and encourage them to use #Captioned

00:33:45.842 --> 00:33:48.562
to help expand the video's reach

00:33:48.587 --> 00:33:51.035
or thank them if they used the hashtag.

00:33:51.587 --> 00:33:54.208
Next time you post your video online,

00:33:54.233 --> 00:33:56.741
use #Captioned.

00:33:56.765 --> 00:34:01.055
It's a unique hashtag, because it
doesn't tell you the topic of the video,

00:34:01.080 --> 00:34:03.464
but rather the video has captions.

00:34:03.896 --> 00:34:08.188
One of the biggest barriers to
captioning is not knowing what to do.

00:34:08.745 --> 00:34:13.169
Share captioning how-to
and resources and guidance.

00:34:13.756 --> 00:34:15.573
Captions have changed my life.

00:34:15.850 --> 00:34:20.064
Captions let me know what happened
when I saw breaking news.

00:34:20.573 --> 00:34:22.130
They let me learn something new,

00:34:22.749 --> 00:34:25.368
they let me catch more stories,

00:34:25.828 --> 00:34:28.664
whether it's on video or a video call.

00:34:29.101 --> 00:34:33.488
It's only recently that I've ventured
into the world of video calls,

00:34:33.513 --> 00:34:34.759
thanks to captions.

00:34:35.283 --> 00:34:39.011
You can learn more about
that at meryl.net/calls.

00:34:39.670 --> 00:34:42.833
Feel free to connect with me
and send me your questions.

00:34:42.857 --> 00:34:47.894
You can find everything and
more at meryl.net/captions.

00:34:48.386 --> 00:34:50.256
And I welcome any feedback

00:34:50.280 --> 00:34:54.009
on what could be added removed
or changed in this presentation.

00:34:54.950 --> 00:34:56.454
Thank you for your time.

00:34:56.478 --> 00:35:00.275
I want to send a Texas-style
thank you and yee haw

00:35:00.300 --> 00:35:03.734
to the WordPress Accessibility Day team
for having me,

00:35:03.759 --> 00:35:08.488
to the sponsors you for making
the event and human captions possible

00:35:08.513 --> 00:35:13.146
and to the amazing captioner
who captioned this accent.

00:35:13.171 --> 00:35:15.369
Now let's hear from y'all.

00:35:16.130 --> 00:35:19.040
<v David> That was awesome.
Meryl did an amazing job.

00:35:19.064 --> 00:35:20.558
It's super incredible.

00:35:20.582 --> 00:35:22.369
We're gonna go to the questions

00:35:22.394 --> 00:35:25.304
so I'll get the questions
ready here for Meryl,

00:35:25.328 --> 00:35:26.906
and I'll read it out loud here:

00:35:26.931 --> 00:35:30.438
So I've heard you present
and mention Disney's Hamilton

00:35:30.462 --> 00:35:33.060
being so impactful with their users—

00:35:33.085 --> 00:35:35.184
or with their use of captions,

00:35:35.208 --> 00:35:39.177
because traditional musicals may not
be as accessible as needed.

00:35:39.717 --> 00:35:43.444
Can you share another development
in captioning or technology

00:35:43.468 --> 00:35:46.287
i.e. voice to text on mobile phones,

00:35:46.312 --> 00:35:48.204
that has been impactful for you?

00:35:48.847 --> 00:35:52.600
<v Meryl> Well the Hamilton's a big deal
for me, because I love that show

00:35:52.847 --> 00:35:53.958
and I love Broadway.

00:35:53.982 --> 00:35:56.930
Believe it or not, even though I'm deaf,
I love musicals

00:35:56.955 --> 00:36:00.827
and I knew I would never be able
to see Hamilton on stage,

00:36:00.852 --> 00:36:03.566
because it is so fast.

00:36:03.591 --> 00:36:07.279
So I was so grateful when
Disney decided to bring it sooner.

00:36:07.647 --> 00:36:11.000
As for another development
in captioning or technology

00:36:11.025 --> 00:36:14.331
I have to say
the video calls that I mentioned,

00:36:14.356 --> 00:36:18.725
because before the pandemic,
I never did video call,

00:36:18.750 --> 00:36:21.991
because the couple times I did,
it was a bad experience.

00:36:22.015 --> 00:36:24.126
Now I call my mom every week.

00:36:24.150 --> 00:36:26.501
I call a friend every week

00:36:26.526 --> 00:36:28.912
and I join Team meetings

00:36:28.937 --> 00:36:30.132
a couple times a month.

00:36:30.156 --> 00:36:32.683
Actually, I have one
every week that I know.

00:36:33.501 --> 00:36:34.685
Next question.

00:36:34.810 --> 00:36:36.138
<v David> Yes, great.

00:36:36.888 --> 00:36:40.070
All right, so the next question is
how do you—

00:36:40.737 --> 00:36:46.616
I'm sorry, what do you use when you have
a lengthier dialogue for longer videos.

00:36:46.641 --> 00:36:48.188
This can be costly.

00:36:48.680 --> 00:36:51.334
<v Meryl> Well, my videos are never that long,

00:36:51.358 --> 00:36:54.413
because I know people
have too much on their plate.

00:36:54.438 --> 00:36:56.409
There's so many great videos out there.

00:36:56.433 --> 00:36:58.000
So I try to keep them short,

00:36:58.461 --> 00:37:04.766
but it just depends on the resources
and what what you have.

00:37:05.186 --> 00:37:08.000
I mean captioning those
are just all getting cheaper,

00:37:08.024 --> 00:37:10.145
one of them does a dollar a minute.

00:37:10.170 --> 00:37:12.775
And I know that for a one person business,

00:37:12.799 --> 00:37:16.008
a video just 50 minutes
long is gonna cost $50

00:37:16.033 --> 00:37:17.744
and that might be a bit much.

00:37:18.549 --> 00:37:20.577
So one way to do it,

00:37:20.601 --> 00:37:23.989
is to try to do script and then
you can copy and paste the script.

00:37:24.014 --> 00:37:25.950
Oh, here's what you can do.

00:37:25.974 --> 00:37:28.580
If you use transcription technology,

00:37:29.834 --> 00:37:32.632
use it to caption your video.

00:37:32.656 --> 00:37:34.949
So let's say I have an app,

00:37:35.675 --> 00:37:37.733
I record my video,

00:37:37.757 --> 00:37:42.259
I let the app listen to the video
and get the transcript.

00:37:42.284 --> 00:37:44.864
Copy and paste that transcript into YouTube

00:37:45.229 --> 00:37:46.864
and see how that works out.

00:37:48.466 --> 00:37:51.244
<v David> Awesome, next question:

00:37:51.957 --> 00:37:57.032
Can you recommend learning resources
for creating effective captions

00:37:57.057 --> 00:37:58.093
for a beginner?

00:37:58.118 --> 00:38:00.771
I want to make sure I can learn properly.

00:38:01.349 --> 00:38:02.700
<v Meryl> That's a great question.

00:38:02.725 --> 00:38:04.367
I just recommend—

00:38:05.468 --> 00:38:10.266
unfortunately, I recommend
you go to my meryl.net/captions,

00:38:10.290 --> 00:38:13.467
because I have a whole
table of contents at the beginning

00:38:13.492 --> 00:38:16.520
and it covers the
10 things we just talked about.

00:38:16.544 --> 00:38:19.324
So you can go to
where you need to begin.

00:38:19.349 --> 00:38:22.897
I haven't seen any that stood out to me

00:38:22.922 --> 00:38:26.393
in terms of teaching "how",

00:38:26.418 --> 00:38:28.364
other than the resources I've provided

00:38:28.388 --> 00:38:30.248
and I linked to other resources.

00:38:32.178 --> 00:38:35.452
<v David> All right, awesome.
Next question:

00:38:35.477 --> 00:38:39.671
Is it better to use closed captions
or open caption?

00:38:39.695 --> 00:38:41.857
Is there any reason to have both?

00:38:42.396 --> 00:38:44.695
<v Meryl> Excellent, excellent question.

00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:47.232
I always recommend closed captions,

00:38:47.256 --> 00:38:50.815
because it puts the viewer in control.

00:38:51.339 --> 00:38:54.437
For example, if I don't like
the font that they're showing,

00:38:54.461 --> 00:38:56.847
I can change it with closed captions.

00:38:57.224 --> 00:38:58.720
With open captions,

00:38:58.720 --> 00:39:00.659
you can't turn them off and on.

00:39:00.684 --> 00:39:02.055
You can't control them,

00:39:02.079 --> 00:39:05.210
if they're terrible, you can't fix it.

00:39:05.702 --> 00:39:07.246
It affects the readability,

00:39:07.886 --> 00:39:10.715
but if you see some of
my videos on LinkedIn

00:39:10.756 --> 00:39:12.791
some of them have open captions,

00:39:12.816 --> 00:39:19.147
only because LinkedIn has lost
the caption file on some of my videos.

00:39:19.576 --> 00:39:24.106
And for me that's worse
than viewer control,

00:39:24.131 --> 00:39:28.082
because I cannot have any
of my videos not have captions

00:39:28.107 --> 00:39:30.217
because I want to walk the talk.

00:39:30.615 --> 00:39:33.945
So closed captioning is
my first recommendation,

00:39:33.969 --> 00:39:37.371
because it lets the
viewer control the caption.

00:39:40.038 --> 00:39:42.554
<v David> Awesome answer. Next question:

00:39:42.990 --> 00:39:47.352
Who, what company makes great
caption videos that you really like

00:39:47.377 --> 00:39:48.758
or they do really well?

00:39:49.877 --> 00:39:53.659
<v Meryl> Well that,
I'm not—no one sticks out, you know.

00:39:53.683 --> 00:39:56.665
I mean, those captions you see on TV shows

00:39:56.690 --> 00:39:58.479
are really well done,

00:39:58.503 --> 00:40:02.005
but that's how it's been done since 1983.

00:40:02.029 --> 00:40:05.246
There's a reason why
captions haven't changed much,

00:40:05.271 --> 00:40:06.796
because it works.

00:40:06.820 --> 00:40:09.343
You don't want them
distracting from the video.

00:40:09.831 --> 00:40:13.116
And as I mentioned earlier, Peloton,

00:40:13.141 --> 00:40:14.922
see I'm mentioning them again,

00:40:15.323 --> 00:40:17.978
so, their name's getting out there

00:40:18.002 --> 00:40:20.828
and I chose them over
the other brand,

00:40:20.853 --> 00:40:24.003
because I could not read
the other brand's captions.

00:40:26.757 --> 00:40:29.400
<v David> All right, awesome.
Next question:

00:40:29.424 --> 00:40:33.040
What is the most
impactful place to start

00:40:33.040 --> 00:40:36.343
if you're just starting adding captions?

00:40:40.429 --> 00:40:42.864
<v Meryl> I guess my website, again.
[Laughing]

00:40:42.889 --> 00:40:44.322
I'm sorry, but…

00:40:45.230 --> 00:40:49.830
so captioning companies
that do the captioning,

00:40:49.855 --> 00:40:51.486
they have resources,

00:40:51.510 --> 00:40:53.446
but I try not to be biased.

00:40:53.470 --> 00:40:56.488
I don't like to mention
one over the other,

00:40:56.513 --> 00:41:00.032
because I don't want to have
that connection, you know.

00:41:00.057 --> 00:41:02.270
I try to be objective,

00:41:02.295 --> 00:41:05.748
but if you go to the captions company,

00:41:05.772 --> 00:41:07.629
they have some good resources

00:41:07.653 --> 00:41:10.371
and a couple of them are on my guide.

00:41:12.320 --> 00:41:14.875
<v David> Awesome. Next question:

00:41:14.900 --> 00:41:18.312
Any advice for captioning
translated content?

00:41:19.136 --> 00:41:21.169
<v Meryl> Oooh that's a tough one.

00:41:21.194 --> 00:41:23.700
That's why closed captions—

00:41:23.725 --> 00:41:25.859
that's another advantage
of closed captions,

00:41:25.884 --> 00:41:30.054
because it's very easy for somebody
to change the language on there.

00:41:30.503 --> 00:41:32.328
So I—

00:41:33.177 --> 00:41:37.096
I would say start with a closed captions

00:41:37.121 --> 00:41:38.514
with the English file

00:41:38.539 --> 00:41:41.637
and then you can translate it to Spanish.

00:41:41.661 --> 00:41:44.442
And I showed that HTML example,

00:41:44.847 --> 00:41:49.020
so that's how you can
offer examples-- languages.

00:41:49.044 --> 00:41:53.226
And also YouTube can handle
multiple languages as well.

00:41:54.012 --> 00:41:55.453
<v David> Awesome.

00:41:55.477 --> 00:41:59.003
Next question, this is one of my own,
I have so many notes,

00:41:59.028 --> 00:42:04.516
but: If people only remember one thing
from what you presented today,

00:42:04.541 --> 00:42:05.635
what should that be?

00:42:06.674 --> 00:42:08.236
<v Meryl> Caption everything,

00:42:08.285 --> 00:42:14.174
but seriously the second thing I would say
is make sure your captions are readable.

00:42:14.199 --> 00:42:15.314
If they're not readable,

00:42:15.338 --> 00:42:19.579
all that hard work you put
into captioning your videos,

00:42:19.604 --> 00:42:20.738
goes to waste.

00:42:21.992 --> 00:42:23.269
<v David> Thank you, Meryl.